runs.comm: short of a good length outside off, leaves it alone to the keeper
short of a good length on middle, rocks back and turns it to midwicket
slung it towards middle and leg, chipped over midwicket into the deep for a couple of runs
back of a length outside off, punched off the back foot towards extra cover
slightly short on leg stump, tries to turn it down fine but is struck on the pads
back of a length and quick but down the leg side, Mutizwa doesn't get his body behind it either and concedes five wides
shortish on the off, gets back and knocks it down towards point

appeal for lbw, looked really close, McCullum went after that straightish delivery on middle and leg, tried to flick it over square leg, missed and the fielders went up. It looked out to the naked eye, would have hot middle and leg it seemed but the umpire didn't think so. It hit the back leg
good length on the off, driven on the up wide of mid-off for a single
slower legcutter bowled on middle, driven towards midwicket
beautifully clipped, repeats the shot he attempted earlier in the over, except this time he connects, in the slot on middle and leg and it's dispatched over the deep square leg boundary
a slower one bowled slightly short outside off, drops it into the leg side and steals a single
short of a good length on middle, tries to turn it to the leg side, is struck on the hip, steals a single
shortish on the off, drops it down towards point from the crease
bowled it short outside leg and Guptill has a go at it but withdraws at the last moment, there's an appeal for caught-behind, Mpofu thinks he's gloved it but the umpire doesn't, didn't seem like it
short of a good length on middle, knocks it down into the leg side and steals a quick single
connected well, was the slower ball, McCullum charged down the track and smashed it over deep midwicket, there is a fielder in place there but it evaded him
banged it short outside leg stump, it's called a wide, another flying start for the New Zealanders here
shortish on middle, knocks it down gently into the leg side in front of square leg for a single
short of a good length on leg stump, pushed wide of midwicket for a single
goodish length outside off and moves away Guptill tries to strike him through the line, it's a no-ball and therefore a freehit is next
low full toss outside off and Guptill drags it uppishly wide of mid-on for a boundary, had got enough on it though it looked like he'd mistimed it
middled it this time, dropped it short outside off did Jarvis and Guptill hammered it past midwicket for four more
goodish length outside off, chopped it behind point for a single
slower one bowled full on the off, it's driven firmly back to the bowler
short on middle and leg, swivels to whip it square but is struck on the thigh
angling towards leg stump, turned past square leg for a single
short and down the leg side, called a wide
flighted on leg stump, pushed back towards the bowler
flighted, senses a chance, comes down the track and swings it towards deep square leg, on the bounce
firing it on middle, McCullum comes down the track and chips it over extra cover, Taylor gives chase and almost makes a mess of it but manages to drag it in
short on middle and turning towards off, run down towards point
short on leg stump, whipped past square leg for a single
short and wide and it's cut away hard, past point to beat third man to the boundary
yorker length outside off, dug out towards midwicket, called for a single but McCullum rightly sent him back
angling in towards middle, gets across and turns it to midwicket
dropped it short, was the slower one, rolls his wrists over that one and plays it to square leg
aiming for the blockhole again, dug out past the bowler and towards long-on for a single
seems him come down and fires a full toss, whipped towards deep square leg for a single
floating it on the off stump, turning in, gets forward and drops it on the off side
slightly short as he seems him come down, punched back to the bowler
waiting for it to turn in is McCullum, paddles it over the keeper for a couple more
that's disappeared, tossed up, he came down the pitch and took it from the slot, launching it over wide long-on for a big one
shortish on the off, gets across and punches it down to long-on for a single
late-cuts that one towards short third man for a single
waits for it to turn away and guides it to short third man
comes down the track and punches it back to the bowler
short ball on leg stump, pulls it away to deep midwicket for a single
found the gap, Price dropped it short, McCullum charged out, picked the length early and pulled it over midwicket for a boundary
flighted on middle, turned past square leg for a single
fires it quick outside leg stump, that's where McCullum had been standing, tries to turn it away square but is struck on the pads
Guptill's turn this time, Utseya's giving air and they're taking full toll, comes down to the pitch and hits it with the turn over wide long-on on
tossed up outside off, Guptill plays it down to point and there's an overthrow
flighted on middle, pushed towards deep midwicket for a single
short outside off, turning in, cuts it past point for three runs into the deep
will that be called a no-ball for height? Looked  around waist high and he pulled it high and handsome over cow corner. It has been called a no-ball
short on the off, pushed towards extra cover off the back foot
New Zealand are cruising here, comes down the track and wasn't entirely to the pitch for this one but went through with the shot and had the power to take it over the long-on boundary
shortish outside off, knocks it down behind point for a single
good length outside off, gets across and works it into the on side for a single to raise his second consecutive half-century
wide, way wide outside off and it's called
low full toss on middle, worked into that gap between long-on and midwicket for a couple of runs
straying on the pads, fine leg is up, Guptill just tickles it past that fielder for four more, they're piling it on here
short and wide and it's cut hard but uppishly and just short of point
driven on the up wide of extra cover for a single but Taylor, who dives to his right and stops that well, concedes an overthrow
shortish on leg stump, whipped away towards deep square leg for a single
McCullum is unstoppable, charges down the track again, that one's bowled flat and slightly short but he's committed to the shot, hammers it over deep midwicket
short, pulled away towards deep square leg for a single
short again and it's pulled to deep midwicket for a single this time
superbly done, full toss and he had picked his gap, reverse-swept it smartly from the leg stump past short third for four more
dances down the track and drills it towards long-off for a single
bowled'im! Goes for the paddle scoop, it's a straight delivery on middle and he bent low and got out of the way to play it over short fine, didn't connect and it crashed into middle
banged it short on middle, pulled all along the ground to deep square leg for a single
short ball, cut away towards deep point, a fumble by Mpofu in the deep and they come back for the second
full on middle, driven down to long-on for a single
short of a good length outside off, tries to cream it on the up, gets a thick inside edge and sneaks a single
full, yorker length on middle, digs it out wide of square leg and sensing that the fielder is deep enough, scrambles  back for the second and makes it in time
shortish on middle and off, punched to extra cover for a single
full toss on the off, slapped wide of long-on for a single
comes down the track and the bowler chases him, turned straight to midwicket
long hop on leg stump, Jesse gets into position early and pulls him over square leg to find the ropes
chipped past the bowler to long-on for a single
wide open spaces in the field, another full toss from Utseya and he's smashed it over midwicket for a one bounce four, raises his half-century
shortish on middle from round the wicket, punched off the back foot to midwicket
Price gets into the act now, comes down the track and lofts him inside out over extra cover for a boundary
pushed off the back foot to long-on for a single
dropped it short on middle, pulled away to midwicket
tossed up outside leg stump, tries to sweep it down fine, comes off the pad
shortish on the off, cut behind point for a single to keep strike
short of a good length, punched wide of deep cover for a couple of runs
short on middle, pulled towards deep square leg for one more
full on the pads, flicked away towards deep square leg for one more
slower one bowled full on the pads, chipped to deep midwicket for a single, 150 up
short outside off, goes for the pull but doesn't connect, was aiming at midwicket but missed
poor bowling, slower one and it's short on leg stump, Guptill helps it on its way over short fine leg for a boundary
appeal for caught-behind, Jesse attempts the paddle-scoop over short fine but misses, it just goes over the stumps but difficult to determine if there was a nick
poor line, on the pads, short and slow and he whips it comfortably over short fine
goes for the paddle scoop once more but doesn't get hold, the umpire reckons he got an inside edge there
banged in short on the off, pulled wide of long-on for a brace
six, that's punished, short outside off and it's shovelled over the deep midwicket boundary for a flat six
length ball and he gets it over the bowler's head, picks it off a length and launches it wide of long-off for a one bounce four
full outside off, Ryder makes room and steers it to deep point for a single
length ball and he tries to swing that over midwicket but it's miscued, gets a leading edge and he holes out to long-off
turned away towards deep midwicket for a single
swinging in, full on middle, pushed down to long-on for a single
aiming for a yorker again, plays it away past midwicket for a single, right length but he's overstepped according to the umpire, though that looked a little tight, freehit time nevertheless
in the slot for Taylor, it's pitched up and it's absolutely creamed through extra cover for four more
low full toss, pushed towards midwicket who's a little deep and they come back for the second
well bowled, got it right, in the blockhole outside off, Ryder made room to hit that but couldn't make contact
well bowled again, fullish, pushed down the ground for a couple more runs wide of long-off
clipped towards deep square leg for a single
full toss and Taylor's eyes light up, but he can't get it away, just a single to deep square leg
nicely done, low full toss again, Ryder can't do much about it, gets a thick inside edge and just the single
good stuff, almost in the blockhole outside off, can only strike it to long-off, Taylor attempts an impossible second but Coventry returns a good throw and Mutizwa does the rest
